<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h4>0. Open ssh terminal in the VM</h4>
            <pre>vagrant ssh</pre>
        <h4>1. Checking Open Flow Controller Rest Server status</h4>
      {{#if serverOnline}}
          <div class="alert alert-success">
              Open Flow controller REST server is online. Please jump to the next step.
          </div>
      {{else}}
          <div class="alert alert-danger">
              Open Flow controller REST server is offline, please launch it with the following command.
          </div>
          <pre>ryu-manager ./vendor/ryu/ryu/app/ofctl_rest.py</pre>
      {{/if}}
        <h4>2. Launch Mininet in the VM</h4>
        <pre>sudo mn --topo=tree,1,3 --mac --controller=remote --switch ovsk,protocols=OpenFlow13</pre>

        <h4>3. Check Stats menu point and click Switches</h4>
        <p>You should the list of available switches.</p>

        <h4>4. You can add new flow rules with clicking on Add Flow</h4>
        <p>Use the given format for creating Match and Actions.</p>

        <h4>5. Check flows clicking on Stats menu and Flows submenu.</h4>
        <p>You will see all the switches and connected flows.</p>
    </div>
</div>